						               													<description>This original game from Japanese lands swells the catalogs of the murder mystery genre, increasingly widespread in the international recreational arena.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What is a murder mystery?&amp;#10;In this deductive genre, each player plays the role of a character with the dual purpose of clarifying a mystery and simultaneously achieving their own goals. The investigation, the negotiations with the rest of the cast and the exchange of information are fundamental pieces to solve the crime, but we must not forget that the murderer is one of you. You cannot believe everything they tell you, but neither can you win without trusting someone ... Enjoy this unique experience that, although used only once, will leave you wanting more.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;England, late 16th century. A man is found dead in a town in the English countryside, apparently after his executioner plunged his head into the river that runs next to the inn where he was staying. The guests, the white witch so beloved in the municipality and the employees of the establishment themselves look at each other suspiciously trying to identify the culprit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
